<td valign=top > 
<b> Digital Forensics & Tampering</b>
<BR>
<p>
We are <a href="digitaltampering">living in a world</a> where seeing
(or hearing) is no longer believing. The technology that allows for
digital media to be manipulated and distorted is developing at
break-neck speeds. And at the same time, our understanding of the
technological, ethical, and legal implications is lagging behind.  We
are, therefore, developing mathematical and computational algorithms
to detect tampering in digital media (in the absence of any type of
digital watermark or signature). To do so, we quantify statistical
correlations that result from specific forms of digital tampering, and
devise detection schemes to reveal these correlations.
</td>

<td> &nbsp&nbsp </td>

